title: Appointments to Social Welfare Advisory Committee
content_text: The Government today (November 30) announced the appointment of six new members and the re-appointment of the chairman and four incumbent members to the Social Welfare Advisory Committee (SWAC). All appointments will take effect from tomorrow (December 1). The six new members are Mr Quentin Fong King-sang, Mr Herman Hui Chung-shing, Dr Benjamin Lai Sau-shun, Mr Vincent Lo Wing-sang, Mr Tung Chi-fat and Ms Lisa

Yip Sau-wah. They are appointed for a term of two years. Mr Fong is the Assistant Vice-President of Community Relations of Public 
Affairs of Pacific Century Cyber Works Limited (PCCW) who has served in the 
Boys' and Girls' Club Association of Hong Kong before joining the PCCW. Mr Fong 
has been very active in promoting volunteerism. Mr Hui is a consultant solicitor. He is very familiar with welfare 
matters and is currently serving on a number of boards and committees related to

matters and is currently serving on a number of boards and committees related to 
welfare namely, the Council of the Queen Elizabeth Foundation for the Mentally 
Handicapped, the Guardianship Board, the Rehabilitation Advisory Committee and 
the Disciplinary Committee of the Social Workers' Registration Board. Dr Lai is a private practising psychiatrist who has previously worked in 
various public hospitals. He is renowned in the psychiatric field in Hong Kong 
and is currently a member of several welfare-related committees and

and is currently a member of several welfare-related committees and 
advisor/consultant in various welfare organisations. Mr Lo is an experienced solicitor and is well versed with community 
services, such as serving on the Lotteries Fund Advisory Committee, the Hong 
Kong Advisory Council on AIDS, the former District Board and the Social Welfare 
Service Quality Assessment Review Board. As the Executive Director of the Neighbourhood Advice-action Council, Mr 
Tung has rich experience in the social welfare sector and has served on a few 
welfare-related advisory committees such as the Social Work Training Fund

welfare-related advisory committees such as the Social Work Training Fund 
Committee. Ms Yip is a secondary school principal with experience in handling youth 
matters and has served on the district management boards of YMCA and the 
Sub-Committee on Promotion of Student and Youth Volunteering. Meanwhile, the chairman and four incumbent members have been 
re-appointed. The chairman, Mr Wilfred Wong Ying-wai, and three members Mrs 
Cheung Ang Siew-mei, Dr Stephen Chow Chun-kay and Mr Keith Lam Hon-keung are

appointed for a term of two years. Dr Leung Cho-bun is re-appointed for a term 
of one year. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, welcomed the 
appointment of the new members and the re-appointment of the chairman and 
incumbent members. He looked forward to their contribution to the development of 
welfare policy issues. Dr Chow also thanked the five outgoing members - Ms Vivien Chan; Dr 
Darwin Chen; Mr Wilfred Lee Chee-wah, Mr Poon Huen-wai; and Mr Stephen Yau

How-boa - for their contribution to the work of the SWAC during their term of 
appointment. The functions of the SWAC are to keep social welfare services under 
continuous review, and to advise the Government on all matters of social welfare

policy. Following is the membership list of the SWAC as from December 1, 2004: Chairman: Mr Wilfred Wong Ying-wing, JP Members: Mrs Cheung Ang Siew-mei Dr Stephen Chow Chun-kay, BBS, JP Dr Miranda Chung Chan Lai-foon, Ms Christine Fang Meng-sang, JP Mr Quentin Fong King-sang Mr Herman Hui Chung-shing, MH Dr Benjamin Lai Sau-shun, Mr Keith Lam Hon-keung, OBE, JP Dr Leung Cho-bun Mr Vincent Lo Wing-sang, JP Prof Diana Mak Ping-see Mr
